  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: erigon version 2022.99.99-dev-832d9fd3\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux, m5.2xlarge, storage: ssd gp3 2.3T\r\n\r\nCommit hash : \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nMemory usage not peaking.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nMemory usage by erigon process peaks up to 100%, then kswapd0 which swaps data when RAM is running out uses all the CPU resources making the ec2 instance die. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"644\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/95335707/191640044-7c122fe8-ef26-477c-bd2c-4289ea5f3407.png\">\r\n<img width=\"576\" alt=\"image (2)\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/95335707/191640059-2dc5104a-f813-4163-bd05-9297987c9a6e.png\">\r\n\r\nI think there is some kind of memory leak in erigon. \r\nWould you please check if this is ture and make a patch to fix this problem?",
